2026-03-03 | Longest Subarray with At Most Two Distinct Integers

	Question
Given arr[],
return the length of the longest subarray
that contains at most two distinct integers.

	Approach
1.	This is a classic sliding window problem:
		Longest subarray with at most K distinct elements.
2.	Use two pointers:
		left and right.
3.	Maintain a hashmap:
		value → frequency in current window.
4.	Expand right pointer:
		Increment frequency.
5.	If distinct count > 2:
		Shrink window from left
		until distinct count ≤ 2.
6.	Track maximum window size.
7.	Time Complexity:
		O(n)
8.	Space Complexity:
		O(1) (since max distinct ≤ 2)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    int longestSubarray(vector<int>& arr) {
        unordered_map<int, int> freq;
        int left = 0;
        int maxLen = 0;

        for (int right = 0; right < arr.size(); right++) {
            freq[arr[right]]++;

            while (freq.size() > 2) {
                freq[arr[left]]--;
                if (freq[arr[left]] == 0)
                    freq.erase(arr[left]);
                left++;
            }

            maxLen = max(maxLen, right - left + 1);
        }

        return maxLen;
    }
};

	Key Insight
Maintain a sliding window that always satisfies
“at most two distinct”.
Expand when valid, shrink when invalid.
This guarantees an optimal O(n) solution.
